rComments: She is a strict grader and does not accommodate any personal situation. She can be extremely condescending and does not care for her students well being.
Please do not take a course with this Professor. I am warning you.

You're good as long as you do the weekly readings which can be a lot. The in class writings are easy marks. For the papers go to office hours. No final so that's perfect. Lectures are fine. She gives proper logical answers to questions.

rComments: Not the most engaging professor. Though well versed in some matter, not aware of her own privilege, commands the respect of her students by means of condescension. She is not the best teacher in that she does not inspire or demonstrate genuine care in her students progress. I did well because I taught myself.

The prof does not post the lecture slides, and you are not allowed to take pictures either or it's an "academic offence", so you have to be able to type fast, especially because what she says is more important than what's on the slides. There are many readings, this is not a class you want to procrastinate in. Reading material is hard to understand

rComments: Shes a fun prof. but is strict with cellphone use. she will call you right out infront of 200 students for using your cellphone

Professor Karen is one of the nicest and engaging teachers I've ever had. She's always there to help you and she's very open to critique and reflections on the course material from students. She really wants her students to understand and apply the course beyond the classroom setting.
